[{"category":"section","location":"#PyTesseractDecoder.jl","page":"Home","text":"A Julia wrapper for accessing the python library tesseract-decoder.","title":"PyTesseractDecoder.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#How-to-use","page":"Home","text":"The relevant python modules/objects are immediately available:\n\njulia> using PyTesseractDecoder\n\njulia> PyTesseractDecoder.tesseract\nPython: <module 'tesseract_decoder.tesseract' from ...>\n\njulia> PyTesseractDecoder.stim\nPython: <module 'stim' from ...>\n\njulia> PyTesseractDecoder.np\nPython: <module 'numpy' from ...>\n\nYou can also import them into your namespace:\n\njulia> using PyTesseractDecoder: tesseract, stim, np\n\nThis package is separate from PyQDecoders.jl because tesseract-decoder runs on fewer operating systems and breaks the CI of PyQDecoders.jl.","title":"How to use"}]
